= Star-Triangle Relation

There is another relation relating the partition functions of the honeycomb $hl$ and triangle $tl$ lattices. This is the star-triangle relation, by which we relate the Boltzmann weights of the star and triangle units. The honeycomb lattice $hl$ can be comprised of repeating star cells and the triangular lattice $tl$ can be comprised of repeating triangle cells[cf. @starrellab]. The triangle is obtained by summing over the red vertex $l$ in @starrellab, which is the vertex in the center of the star. 

